notes:
Sketch of the eventual DazScript-side client call, worked out before implementation:

DazScript uses DzHttpHelper (its native HTTP client) to call OUT to the daemon,
the reverse of how dazpy's DazClient.execute() calls INTO DAZ Studio today.

  var http = new DzHttpHelper();
  http.setHost("127.0.0.1:18812");
  http.setPath("/run");
  http.setRequestMethod("POST");
  http.setContentType("application/json");
  http.setHeaderValues(["X-DPB-Token"], [token]);  // dazpythonbridge_token.txt, see sop.7
  var responseBytes = http.doSynchronousRequest(body);
  var response = JSON.parse(responseBytes.toString());

Uses doSynchronousRequest (not doAsynchronousRequest + the received signal) to
match /execute's blocking, inline-result style on port 18811.

Proposed response envelope, symmetric with /execute's {success, result, output[], error}:
  { success: true, result: <json>, output: ["print() lines..."], error: "" }

This field-naming/shape choice is NOT yet finalized -- pin it down as part of
implementing this issue so it doesn't get relitigated later.
